Replication of the virus was observed in the trachea and lungs, whereas no virus was found in the spleen for virus control group (
Figure 7
). The pre-treatment group showed a complete reduction of the virus in all the three organs studied. Co and post-treatment groups showed no virus in the lungs and 1-log reduction of the virus in the trachea as compared to virus control. NTZ treated groups had no gross pathological lesions on organs.
